    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                <head>No. 640.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName type="to">Sickles</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 21,
                                        1873</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram, suggesting a possible difference of attitude on the
                                part of Spain in Madrid, and here, which you think calls for your
                                withdrawal from Madrid, and asking a request to the Italian
                                government to authorize its representative to take care of our
                                library at Madrid, has been laid before the President, who decides
                                that public interests require that you should remain at your post
                                until expiration of time heretofore named, or until further orders.
                                If a difference exists, as you suggest, the President feels it his
                                duty to take into consideration the representations made at
                                Washington, which approach most nearly to compliance with our just
                                demands, and he depends upon you to co-operate with our efforts to
                                induce Spain to make such concessions as may avert a rupture between
                                the two republics, without questioning the sincerity of the Madrid
                                cabinet. It will not be possible to send a vessel to Valencia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
